upcoming.name: Hach Code 2020 Tlemcen Hub
upcoming.description:
Hash Code is a team programming competition organized by Google. You pick your team and programming language, we pick a Google engineering problem for you to solve.
Are you up for the challenge?

Top scoring teams from the Online Qualification Round will be notified and invited to the Final Round at Google Dublin on 25th of April!

What do I need to participate?

!!! Important !!!: find a team (2 to 4 people) or contact us to find you a team and be sure you all register at HashCode website (https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode) before 19 Feb 2020, 12:00. You‚Äôll then need to select "GDG Tlemcen Hub" from the list of hubs in the Judge System.

The only thing you need for the Online Qualification Round is a computer. We will announce the problem through a YouTube Live Stream. The Judge System will be available as a web application, compatible with recent web browsers. For the rest of your computer setup, you're free to use the tools and programming languages of your choice.

This year for your convenience we are organising Hash Code in Tlemcen We will provide you guys with the necessary environment and the Internet connection needed so you can connect to Google platform and solve the challenge problems.

Location:
1. HD consulting
Boulevard Khaldi Mohamed, Tlemcen 13000

Agenda:

‚Ä¢ 18:00: Venue opens

‚Ä¢ 18:30: Live stream starts

‚Ä¢ 18:45:Task made available, competition starts

‚Ä¢ 22:30: End of the competition

More info on https://codingcompetitions.withgoogle.com/hashcode/rulesandterms
